posts.title: Poll Worker Training
posts.content:
Salutations, Pedes:

I will be training to be a poll worker next week. I am being trained as an Electronic Voter Identification (EViD) inspector.

I know at least a few of you have experience in this field, and I would greatly appreciate any advice or tips you can share to help me be a good EViD inspector.

Here is a description of the roles and responsibilities I found online.

Greets voters, check each voter's photo & signature ID, verify the voter information on the Electronic Voter Identification Unit (EViD), and issues the voter a ballot. It also assists with the setup/breakdown of equipment. Must be comfortable using a computer-based poll register.

Thank you

EDIT: I also want to add that I'm fluent in a few other languages (most people don't know this), so I will listen intently.

EDIT #2: I forgot to mention that I do have a small camera that I will be using, plus two spare batteries.
